Neighbor count (NC) The central idea behind the neighbor count algorithm is that the number of neighboring amino acids is inversely proportional to the exposure of an amino acid. The definition of a “neighbor” is expanded in this work by assigning a weight between 0.0 and 1.0 to all amino acids in the protein model based on their proximity to the amino acid of interest. A lower boundary and an upper boundary are chosen such that all amino acids whose \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
